reviews.text: The food is cheap but the quality of it was just mediocre... I would suggest tourist to rather go for Cafe de corol, worth the price even though it's a fast food restaurant.

Very normal tea house...

Guess tourists visit here is probably because of Choi hung estate. This Cha Chan Teng is definitely over rated in dazhong!

The price is cheap comparing with high expenditure in Hk. But price to performance ratio is Low comparing with the same standard in SG.

The tomato pork steak rice with egg is normal. There is a Long fat on the steak which make the texture oily.
good!
The food quality is fair but cheap price. Worth to try both the food and the old Hong Kong style cafe.

I had a chance to visit this place thanks to a local friend. It's a truly authentic Hong Kong cafe experience. We ordered some tea and, toast, and a pineapple bun. I've had these food at some other places, but it's definitely not the same as the one I had here.

I didn't see any English menu, so you might have some trouble ordering if you don't come with a local. As always, pointing at what you want should work. The atmosphere is casual and laid back, but you will see the staff moving at some urgency. That's just the way it is. Overall I had a pleasant experience.

座落於九龍一個很舊的公共屋村上，但這個屋村非常出名，名叫彩虹村，很多遊客到此打卡，鑽石冰室在此開業已有40年或以上歷史，屬平民化的茶餐廳，價錢都平民化，食材用料中上，但服務員與廚師的服務態度，都不是用心去做的，有空可到此一遊

今日同位朋友去鑽石冰室食下午茶！
有位呀姐落單
我朋友叫咗份奶油多熱好立克
我叫咗份沙牛麵及凍檸檬茶
呀姐重覆咗單
之後我朋友果份到咗
我份沙牛麵都到咗
但係我杯凍檸茶未到
我只係問咗聲有杯凍檸茶未到
然後有位呀姐話睇我張單
單上寫咗汽水！！
個呀姐話我你係叫汽水！！
我話吓！！！
我明明叫咗凍檸茶，妳哋重覆咗單對住我講凍檸茶
之後就攞咗杯冇人要嘅比我
重要話我傻嘅！！！
服務超差
啲呀姐說話有問題，禍從口出
我唔會再去！！！！
抵食有人情味港式茶餐廳，$17菠蘿油跟熱飲一杯又或$19/一個西多士茶餐，今時今日相信在九龍中交通方便位置，企理装修有冷氣，已近"失踪"，但你仲何以在這找到..哈哈驚喜

社區裡的冰室 真的太復古 可愛
來吃的人都是附近居民
整體環境看起來 是港劇無誤
食物的話 就是簡單 還有午餐special 
阿姨的服務 很不意外的有點兇狠
但閑聊兩句之後 馬上變得很友善 可愛
喜歡這種走入當地生活 沒有觀光客的店
一間有幾十年歷史嘅冰室相信響彩虹邨都好多人識 食物就冇乜嘢突出呀 不過佢可以見證彩虹邨嘅變遷

This colorful public housing estate is a hotbed of would-be social media influencers, yet it's unique style is nonetheless engaging for most anyone. The colors are a bit faded, but it's still interesting to see this place where normal, everyday people live.
Pastel building

This place is not suitable for non photographer.

This estate is one of the most popular landmarks in Honghong is probably HK has nothing to visit. But comparing with no.1 landmark Disney here, this Choi Hung is at least heritage.

For singaporeans, you may ignore this place as it’s not much different from HDB. See my 3rd image taken in SG. This is just a residential area. The building is not as colorful as you see in Photographers photos. You must use filter to make it look better.

For tourists who live in other style architectural complex, you may visit here to feel the locals. Photographers may take 2 hours here to shoot, however, for normal tourists they might just spend 20min... whether you can take great photos in Choi Hung depends on how you shoot and PS. 

My HK Brother-in-law was surprised that I made this place as a HK landmark. But he didn’t know suicide cliff either. Whether this place is worth a visit depends on what your focus in your trip. 

It’s easy to come here as there is a train station called Choi Hung Estate. There are 2 estates near this station to shoot for Photographers. There are several small landmarks in HK which require a lot of time to travel and shoot.

Yeah the building was famous on Instagram that's why we went to check,  unfortunately the colors are almost fading (not as colorful as we expected like we've seen on Instagram). The building still looks cool tho.

If you take the bus, just walk into the choi hung estate gate and turn right. Walk pass the shops, cross the road, turn left, go straight and turn right. You will see the car park. Just go up the stairs and you will see the basketball court. :)

原本想放棄 感覺很多人都來過
加上我住天后 看起來 坐地鐵真的很遙遠
沒想到 uber 只要 20分鐘 台幣大概500可以抵達
節省時間 馬上衝！
還好有來 非常可愛。 就算是陰天 也可以感受到繽紛的氛圍
顏色沒有圖片看起來鮮豔 來這裡大家真的比賽 修圖 調色 對水平
但 整體來說 沒來過的人 還是可以來一下
體驗藝術生活。
